---
import ApiPageHeader from "../components/ApiPageHeader.astro";
import ApiPanel from "../components/ApiPanel.astro";
import { BASE_URL, SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY } from "../model.ts";

const markdown = `# Authentication

Every \`/v1\` resource uses a bearer token from the host process.

Start the host with \`npm run runtime:host\`. It binds \`${BASE_URL}\`, prints one token per process on stdout as \`authorizationToken\`, and serves loopback only. Browser clients must match an explicit origin allowlist.

## Authorization

\`Authorization: Bearer <token>\`: compared exactly against the issued token. Missing or wrong tokens return 401.

The private media route authorizes by grant secret instead of the bearer token.

## First-win smoke

After the token prints, the Overview smoke sequence proves auth through journal poll without claiming captions or SaaS:

\`\`\`bash
${SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY}
\`\`\`
`;
---

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-auth-heading">
  <ApiPageHeader
    title="Authentication"
    headingId="api-auth-heading"
    description="Bearer token from the host you run. Loopback only; browser clients also need an origin allowlist."
    markdown={markdown}
  />
  <p>
    Start the host with <code>npm run runtime:host</code>; it binds <code>127.0.0.1:4312</code>,
    prints one token per process on stdout as <code>authorizationToken</code>, and serves only that
    loopback address. Browser clients must also match an explicit origin allowlist; wildcard origins
    are rejected.
  </p>
  <div class="api-meta">
    <span class="api-meta-label">Base URL</span>
    <code>{BASE_URL}</code>
    <span class="api-meta-note">self-hosted</span>
  </div>
  <div class="api-field">
    <div class="api-field-head">
      <code class="api-field-name">Authorization</code>
      <span class="api-tag">string</span>
      <span class="api-tag">header</span>
      <span class="api-tag api-tag-required">required</span>
    </div>
    <p class="api-field-note">
      <code>Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code>, compared exactly against the token the host issued.
      Missing or wrong tokens return 401. The <a href="/api/playback/">private media route</a> is
      the one exception; it authorizes by grant secret instead, so media elements can stream.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="api-split">
    <div>
      <h2 id="api-auth-smoke-heading">First-Win Smoke</h2>
      <p>
        Same sequence as <a href="/api/">Overview</a>: list sources, plan, start, poll events to
        terminal. Proves the local host without claiming captions, upload CDN, or multi-tenant SaaS.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="api-panels">
      <ApiPanel title="Smoke · Local Host" body={SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY} />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
